## Code Simplification Report

### Changes Made

#### 1. Extract duration once per session, reuse in bucketing
**File**: `src/server/routers/analytics.ts:24-40`
**Type**: Removed redundancy
**Before**:
```ts
const durations = sessions.map(s =>
  (s.endedAt.getTime() - s.startedAt.getTime()) / 1000
);
const maxDuration = Math.max(...durations);

for (let t = 0; t <= maxDuration; t += bucketSeconds) {
  const count = sessions.filter(s => {
    const dur = (s.endedAt.getTime() - s.startedAt.getTime()) / 1000;
    return dur > t;
  }).length;
  buckets.push({ bucketStart: t, listenersRemaining: count / sessions.length });
}
```
**After**:
```ts
const durations = sessions.map(s =>
  (s.endedAt.getTime() - s.startedAt.getTime()) / 1000
);
const maxDuration = Math.max(...durations);

for (let t = 0; t <= maxDuration; t += bucketSeconds) {
  const count = durations.filter(dur => dur > t).length;
  buckets.push({ bucketStart: t, listenersRemaining: count / durations.length });
}
```
Reuses the already-computed `durations` array instead of recomputing each session's duration inside every bucket iteration. Behavior identical (`durations.length === sessions.length`); the inner `.getTime()` recomputation is gone.

